# MPU — MV3 extension rules

- Manifest V3 only. No remote code, no `eval`, no `unsafe-eval` CSP.
- Keep permissions minimal (`storage` preferred). Justify any new permission in `docs/privacy.md` and `store/privacy-practices.md`.
- `web_accessible_resources.matches` must stay limited to PeopleSoft `psp`/`psc` patterns — never `*://*/*`.
- Do not add a Chrome Web Store private `key` to the manifest.
- No jQuery. Prefer TypeScript modules under `src/`.
- Page-context access goes through small `src/inject/*` files only.
- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run test:unit` before committing multi-file changes.
